     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <head>TO THE CHRISTIAN READER.</head>
   <p>
      <hi>Contradicunt linguae multae: diuersae hereses, diuersa schismata sonant: Multa linguae contradicunt veraci doctrinae <gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 word">
            <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
         </gap> curre ad tabernaculū Dei: Ecclesiā Catholicam tene, &amp; protegeris<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="2 letters">
            <desc>••</desc>
         </gap> tabernaculo a contradictione linguarum: August. in Psalm.</hi> 30.</p>
   <p>Many tongues do gayne say: diuerse heresies, diuerse schismes do sounde euery where. Many tongues speake against the true doctrine. Runne thou to the tabernacle of God. Keepe the Catholique church, and thou shalt be defended in the tabernacle from contradiction of tongues.</p>
</div>
